<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Salina:
[B]I'm my guild's leader as well..

And actually, if someone sent me that email I would definitely question the person involved, and talk to the person who sent me the email online if possible.

I take that very seriously, though.  My guild has a good reputation as being a group of people who know what they're doing, so something like that would definitely get my attention.

It reminds me of a point several months ago when someone sent me a tell while I was playing my alt.  He asked me who my guild leader was, and I gave him my main character's name (didn't know what it was about at first).  I asked him what was wrong, and he told me that one of my members (and a good friend of mine) had killed him without provocation in the Arena.

After further questioning, it turned out that there had been a GM event and mass slaughter for fun in the Arena.  This guy had been there for another reason, and my friend as well as a few remaining folks who were killing each other for fun had indeed killed him.

I told my friend, who had since logged in another character to log back in and pay the kid what he had paid for the port to get back to his body.

It turned out that my friend didn't really have much to do with the "murder" of this newbie, but I made sure he was happy with being paid back for the port he had to get.

Was it my fault?  No.  Was it something I had the power to fix?  Yes. 
[/B][/QUOTE]

